task.summary: Basically just minor changes and settings adjustments. # Please enter the commit message for your changes. Lines starting # with '#' will be ignored, and an empty message aborts the commit. # On branch master # Changes to be committed: # new file: .idea/inspectionProfiles/Project_Default.xml # new file: .idea/inspectionProfiles/profiles_settings.xml # modified: .idea/workspace.xml # modified: src/main/Main.java #

Added BackupJob class that creates backup jobs for further processing. # Please enter the commit message for your changes. Lines starting # with '#' will be ignored, and an empty message aborts the commit. # On branch master # Changes to be committed: # new file: .idea/inspectionProfiles/Project_Default.xml # new file: .idea/inspectionProfiles/profiles_settings.xml # modified: .idea/workspace.xml # modified: src/main/Main.java #

All arguments specified for now. Cleaned up a little. Ready to implement the backup manager itself. # Please enter the commit message for your changes. Lines starting # with '#' will be ignored, and an empty message aborts the commit. # On branch master # Changes to be committed: # new file: .idea/inspectionProfiles/Project_Default.xml # new file: .idea/inspectionProfiles/profiles_settings.xml # modified: .idea/workspace.xml # modified: src/main/Main.java #
Did some refactoring and created the BackupManager and BackupInstance classes and started to implement the core functionality.
Added two Enum classes to hold some constant program information.
Set values of the enum classes as static and final. Created the deserialization method for the BackupManager.
Imported enums as static for cleaner code. Created and started implementation of the BackupFileVisitor that traverses the input directory tree and creates backups as needed.
Corrected bugs and made a few practical changes.
Implemented the deletion of backups that are no longer present in the original directory. Hunted a few bugs and hopefully just made it a bit better ;]
Moved all methods for copying/moving/modifying files from BackupFileVisitor to BackupInstance.
Implemented the shallow backup + a bit of tweaking and refactoring never hurt anybody. Hunted down a few bugs too.
A few tweaks here and there. Improved the DeleteFileVisitor - it doesn't care about non-index files and leaves them in the backup directory.
Implemented the synchronization option + a few tweaks here and there.
Added a created artifact for the output jar file.
Hunted down a few bugs and made a few adjustments.
